'''''Haumania''''' is a genus of plants native to Japan, New Guinea and central Africa.<ref>[http://apps.kew.org/wcsp/namedetail.do?name_id=248001 Kew World Checklist of Selected Plant Families, ''Haumania'']</ref><ref>Jean Joseph Gustave Léonard. 1949. Bulletin du Jardin Botanique de l'État à Bruxelles 19: 453</ref> It contains 5 recognized species:

*''[[Haumania danckelmaniana]]'' <small>(J.Braun & K.Schum.) Milne-Redh.,</small> Kew Bull. 5: 162 (1950). - Africa (Central African Republic, Cameroon, Equatorial Guinea, Gabon, Congo-Brazzaville, Congo-Kinshasa) 
*''[[Haumania leonardiana]]'' <small>C.M.Evrard & Bamps,</small> Bull. Jard. Bot. État Bruxelles 29: 370 (1959). - Congo-Kinshasa
*''[[Haumania liebrechtsiana]]'' <small>(De Wild. & T.Durand) J.Léonard,</small> Bull. Jard. Bot. État Bruxelles 19: 454 (1949). - Africa ([[Cabinda Province|Cabinda]], Gabon, Congo-Brazzaville, Congo-Kinshasa) 
*''[[Haumania microphylla]]'' <small>Hoogland</small>, Blumea, Suppl. 4: 228 (1958). - New Guinea
*''[[Haumania walkeri]]'' <small>Ohwi</small>, J. Jap. Bot. 33: 212 (1958). - Japan

